# Technical Specification: AI "Command Center" Module

## 1. System Overview
The **Command Center** is a strategic orchestration layer within the dashboard. It allows users to initiate high-level **Missions** which are processed by an **Orchestrator Agent** (via OpenClaw). The Orchestrator decomposes these missions into executable plans carried out by specialized **Taskforce Agents**.

## 2. Core Components

### A. Navigation & Tabs
- **Location:** New nav-item "Command Center" positioned below the Dashboard.
- **Dynamic Tabs:** Each tab (e.g., *Marketing*, *Operations*) is dynamically generated based on Superadmin configurations.
- **Agent Binding:** Each tab is bound to a specific **Orchestrator Agent** (e.g., `marketing-orchestrator`).

### B. Mission Management (Session-based)
- **Mission:** A single objective or session (e.g., "Improve website traffic by 30%").
- **Execution Modes (Checkboxes):**
    - `[ ] Approve Plan Before Launch`: Execution pauses until a user reviews the generated `.md` plan.
    - `[ ] Auto-Pilot Mode`: Immediate deployment after plan generation.
- **Constraints:** All plans must be built using available agents and within a **Fixed Budget**. Budget will be used to run ad campigns on google, meta etc or sending emails.

## 3. Data Models

### Mission
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `mission_id` | UUID | Primary Key |
| `title` | String | User-defined command |
| `status` | Enum | `Draft`, `Planning`, `WaitingApproval`, `In-Progress`, `Completed`, `Rejected` |
| `plan_doc` | File Path | Link to the `.md` plan file |
| `budget_cap` | Decimal | Maximum financial resource allocation |
| `orchestrator_id` | String | ID of the assigned Orchestrator Agent |

### Plan (.md file)
The plan is a structured Markdown document containing:
- **Strategy Overview:** The "How" of the execution.
- **Taskforce Mapping:** Which agents are being used.
- **Cost Estimate:** Projected spend per task.
- **Milestones:** Key checkpoints for the user.

## 4. UI/UX Design

### Mission Control Layout (Split Pane)
- **Left Pane (Mission Creator):**
    - Text area for natural language input.
    - Checkboxes for approval workflow.
    - Budget input field.
    - "Create Mission" primary action button.
- **Right Pane (Mission History/List):**
    - Scrollable list of active and past missions.
    - Status indicators and quick filters (e.g., "Needs Approval").

### Mission Detail View
- **Main Tab (Analytics):**
    - Aggregated dashboard view.
    - Real-time data visualization pulled from all participating Taskforce Agents (e.g., Google Analytics, Ad Spend, etc.).
- **Plan Tab:**
    - Markdown renderer for the execution plan.
    - Interactive "Approve" or "Reject" buttons.
- **Task View:**
    - A tree or list of child tasks created by the Orchestrator and their individual statuses.

## 5. Workflow Logic
1. **Input:** User sends a command via the Left Pane.
2. **Planning:** Orchestrator calls **OpenClaw** to generate a strategy within budget. (same as tasks via runner)
3. **Approval:** If mandated, the system waits for the user to set status to `Approved`.
4. **Task Dispatch:** Orchestrator creates multiple child tasks and assigns them to **Taskforce Agents** (who have built-in analytics capabilities).
5. **Monitoring:** The Mission Detail View aggregates telemetry from all sub-agents into the central Analytics tab.

## 6. Superadmin Capabilities
- **Tab Management:** Create new tabs in the Command Center.
- **Agent Mapping:** Link an Orchestrator Agent to a specific Command Center Tab.